					<note>
						<hi rend="bold">Note concerning author: </hi>Muḥammad Ṣāliḥ Lahurī is almost certainly <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_270970434">Muḥammad Ṣāliḥ Kambūh</persName>, biographer of <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_13108102">Shāhjahān</persName> and teacher of <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_6178410">Aurangzeb</persName> who died c.1674, author of the <title>ʿAmal-i Ṣāliḥ = Shāhjahān nāmah</title>. The preface of the BL copy (Or. 178) is by <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_306124845">Abū al-Barakāt, known as Munīr</persName> whose own letters are in King's 17.
					</note>
